    "title": "Selected peer in the \"Peers\" tab gets unselected if any previous peer disconnects",
    "body": "On master(209974d379e5c2f32f9f691c992a2fb58be2abf2) the selected peer in the \"Peers\" tab gets unselected if any previous peer (in the upper rows) disconnects.\r\n\r\n**Step 1** -- connected three peers, and \"peerC\" has been selected:\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-12-22 15-04-19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32963518/102891836-92ca8c00-4467-11eb-957c-bf6f25ed917c.png)\r\n\r\n**Step 2** -- new connected peers (\"peerD\") do not hurt:\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-12-22 15-04-30](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32963518/102891955-ca393880-4467-11eb-954a-b5a7d75b5e71.png)\r\n\r\n**Step 3** -- but disconnection of any peer from upper rows (e.g., \"peerB\") causes the loss of peer selection:\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-12-22 15-05-28](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32963518/102892156-2439fe00-4468-11eb-913e-100e096cb0d9.png)\r\n",
